msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:3
msgid ""
"The Linked Data Explorer is a monorepo with two packages: a React frontend "
"SPA and a Node.js/Express backend API. The frontend renders in the browser; "
"the backend handles SPARQL queries, Operaton calls, and chain orchestration."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:7
msgid "System architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:9
msgid ""
"Browser\n"
"  └── Frontend (React + TypeScript, Azure Static Web Apps)\n"
"            │ HTTPS/REST\n"
"  └── Backend (Node.js + Express, Azure App Service)\n"
"            ├── SPARQL ──────► TriplyDB (knowledge graph)\n"
"            └── REST API ────► Operaton (DMN execution engine)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:18
msgid ""
"The frontend never calls TriplyDB or Operaton directly in production. All "
"calls go through the backend, which handles authentication, CORS, caching, "
"and variable orchestration. In local development, the frontend can also use "
"a CORS proxy fallback for public SPARQL endpoints."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:22
msgid "Frontend architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:24
msgid ""
"The frontend is a single-page application with no routing library. "
"Navigation state is managed as an enum (`ViewMode`) in the top-level "
"`App.tsx`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:26
msgid ""
"App.tsx\n"
"├── Sidebar navigation (ViewMode selector)\n"
"├── QueryEditor view\n"
"│   ├── SparqlEditor (query input)\n"
"│   ├── ResultsTable (tabular results)\n"
"│   └── GraphView (D3.js force-directed graph)\n"
"├── ChainBuilder view\n"
"│   ├── DmnList (available DMNs, left panel)\n"
"│   ├── ChainComposer (drag-drop zone, centre panel)\n"
"│   │   └── SemanticAnalysis tab\n"
"│   ├── ChainConfig (inputs + execution, right panel)\n"
"│   │   ├── InputForm\n"
"│   │   ├── ExecutionProgress\n"
"│   │   ├── ChainResults\n"
"│   │   └── ExportChain (JSON / BPMN 2.0)\n"
"│   └── ValidationPanel\n"
"├── BpmnModeler view\n"
"│   ├── ProcessList (left panel)\n"
"│   ├── BpmnCanvas (bpmn-js wrapper, centre)\n"
"│   │   └── Deploy modal (one-click Operaton deployment)\n"
"│   └── BpmnProperties (right panel)\n"
"│       ├── DmnTemplateSelector (BusinessRuleTask)\n"
"│       └── FormTemplateSelector (UserTask / StartEvent)  ← new in v1.0.0\n"
"├── FormEditor view                                       ← new in v1.0.0\n"
"│   ├── FormList (left panel)\n"
"│   └── FormCanvas (@bpmn-io/form-js editor, centre)\n"
"└── Changelog / Help view"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:56
msgid ""
"The `FormEditor` view and `BpmnModeler` view share the `FormService` "
"localStorage layer — forms authored in `FormEditor` are immediately "
"available to `FormTemplateSelector` in the BPMN properties panel with no "
"explicit synchronisation step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:58
msgid ""
"State is managed with React hooks at the component level. There is no global "
"state library. The `templateService.ts` utility provides the only persistent "
"state — localStorage CRUD for chain templates and BPMN processes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:62
msgid "Backend architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:64
msgid ""
"The backend is a structured Express application following the Dutch "
"Government API Design Rules (API-20, API-57)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:66
msgid ""
"src/\n"
"├── index.ts              entry point, server startup\n"
"├── routes/\n"
"│   ├── index.ts          registers all route groups\n"
"│   ├── dmn.routes.ts     GET /v1/dmns, /v1/dmns/chains, /v1/dmns/semantic-"
"equivalences\n"
"│   ├── chain.routes.ts   POST /v1/chains/execute, POST /v1/chains/export\n"
"│   ├── triplydb.routes.ts POST /v1/triplydb/query\n"
"│   └── health.routes.ts  GET /v1/health\n"
"├── services/\n"
"│   ├── sparql.service.ts       SPARQL queries against TriplyDB\n"
"│   ├── operaton.service.ts     Operaton REST API calls\n"
"│   ├── orchestration.service.ts chain execution and variable mapping\n"
"│   └── triplydb.service.ts     direct TriplyDB proxy (dynamic endpoints)\n"
"├── middleware/\n"
"│   ├── cors.ts\n"
"│   └── errorHandler.ts\n"
"└── utils/\n"
"    ├── logger.ts         Winston structured logging\n"
"    └── config.ts         environment config with validation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:88
msgid ""
"Legacy `/api/*` routes exist with deprecation headers for backward "
"compatibility. All new work uses `/v1/*`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:92
msgid "Data flow — chain execution"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:94
msgid ""
"1. Frontend POST /v1/chains/execute\n"
"   { chain: [dmnId1, dmnId2], inputs: {...}, endpoint: \"...\" }\n"
"\n"
"2. orchestration.service.ts\n"
"   for each DMN in chain:\n"
"     a. sparql.service.ts → fetch DMN metadata from TriplyDB (cached 5 min)\n"
"     b. Flatten previous step outputs into current step inputs\n"
"     c. operaton.service.ts → POST /engine-rest/decision-definition/key/{id}/"
"evaluate\n"
"     d. Collect and flatten results\n"
"\n"
"3. Return combined results to frontend"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:110
msgid "Caching"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:112
msgid ""
"The backend caches DMN metadata per endpoint with a 5-minute TTL. The cache "
"key is the endpoint URL. Switching endpoints in the frontend bypasses the "
"cache and triggers a fresh SPARQL query."
msgstr ""

