msgid "Pending-until-Save editing model"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:485
msgid ""
"Footer edits — `language`, `organization`, `ropaRef`, `dsoActiviteitUrn` — "
"accumulate in a draft on `BpmnModeler.tsx` rather than persisting "
"immediately. The pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:487
msgid ""
"type FooterDraft = {\n"
"  language?: BpmnProcess['language'];\n"
"  organization?: string;\n"
"  ropaRef?: string;\n"
"  dsoActiviteitUrn?: string;\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"const [draft, setDraft] = useState<FooterDraft>({});\n"
"const [hasFooterChanges, setHasFooterChanges] = useState(false);\n"
"const [hasCanvasChanges, setHasCanvasChanges] = useState(false);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:500
msgid "Footer handlers update only the draft:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:502
msgid ""
"const handleLanguageChange = (language: string | undefined) => {\n"
"  if (!activeProcessId) return;\n"
"  setDraft((d) => ({ ...d, language: language as BpmnProcess['language'] }))"
";\n"
"  setHasFooterChanges(true);\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:510
msgid ""
"`handleSaveProcess` flushes the draft into both the in-memory `BpmnProcess` "
"object and the BPMN XML's `ronl:` attributes, then resets the draft. "
"Distinguishing \"user touched the field\" from \"user explicitly cleared "
"it\" matters — the `'language' in draft` idiom preserves the difference "
"between *unset* and *cleared*:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:512
msgid "language: 'language' in draft ? draft.language : process.language,"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:516
msgid ""
"The list panel reads from committed `processes` state so visible grouping "
"doesn't shift while the user is typing in the footer. The footer reads its "
"display value via a `readEffective()` helper: draft wins when the field has "
"been touched, else the committed `BpmnProcess` field, else the `ronl:` "
"attribute extracted from the XML."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:518
msgid ""
"Navigation guards (`handleCreateProcess`, `handleLoadProcess`, "
"`handleCloseProcess`) check the combined `hasUnsavedChanges = "
"hasCanvasChanges || hasFooterChanges` and prompt the user to confirm before "
"discarding. `BpmnCanvas` exposes its own dirty state via `onDirtyChange?: "
"(dirty: boolean) => void` so the parent can combine canvas content edits "
"with footer edits into a single guard."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:520
msgid "`applyRonlAttr` helper"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:522
msgid ""
"A single helper consolidates the four duplicated XML-mutation snippets that "
"previously lived in each footer handler. It ensures the `xmlns:ronl=` "
"namespace is declared on `<definitions>`, then either rewrites an existing "
"`ronl:<attr>=` value, injects a new attribute on the `<bpmn:process>` "
"opening tag, or strips the attribute when the value is `undefined`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:524
msgid ""
"function applyRonlAttr(xml: string, attr: string, value: string | undefined)"
": string;"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:528
msgid ""
"`handleSaveProcess` calls it once per draft field present (`language`, "
"`organization`, `ropaRef`, `dsoActiviteitUrn`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:530
msgid "Shell → subprocess atomic save"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:532
msgid ""
"After saving a shell, `handleSaveProcess` walks `processes` for subprocesses "
"where `processRole === 'subprocess'` and `calledElement === "
"shell.bpmnProcessId`. For each match, the shell's `language` and "
"`organization` are applied to the subprocess XML (via `applyRonlAttr`) and "
"to the in-memory `BpmnProcess` fields, then persisted via "
"`BpmnService.saveProcess` in sequence. The propagation triggers on every "
"shell save when the shell has either field set, regardless of whether the "
"user touched the footer in this session — the architectural rule \"shell "
"wins\" must hold across editing sessions."
msgstr ""

