msgid ""
"The seed document (`Kapvergunning Beschikking`) is stored at `public/"
"examples/flevoland/kapvergunning-beschikking.document` and loaded on first "
"launch via `exampleVersions.ts`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:100
msgid ""
"export const EXAMPLE_VERSIONS: Record<string, number> = {\n"
"  'kapvergunning-beschikking': 1,\n"
"  // ...\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:107
msgid ""
"The app checks `localStorage` key `linkedDataExplorer_exampleVersions`. If "
"the stored version for a key is lower than `EXAMPLE_VERSIONS[key]`, the "
"example file is re-fetched and written (as `readonly: true`, `status: "
"'example'`). This allows updating example content for existing users by "
"incrementing the version number — no `localStorage` clear required."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:109
msgid ""
"**Developer workflow:** edit the example in `public/examples/flevoland/`, "
"mirror the change to `examples/organizations/flevoland/`, increment the "
"version in `exampleVersions.ts`, commit."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:113
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\document-composer.md:113"
msgid "Drag-and-drop"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:115
msgid ""
"Drag-and-drop is implemented with `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable`. "
"The `DndContext` lives in `DocumentComposer.tsx` and passes `dragEndEvent` "
"down to `DocumentCanvas.tsx` via props (to keep business logic in the canvas "
"component while the context wraps the full three-panel layout)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:117
msgid "Two drag types are distinguished via `DragData.type`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:119
msgid ""
"`'new-block'` — dragged from the Content library. Resolved in "
"`DocumentCanvas` by calling `createBlock(dragData)` and appending to the "
"target zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:120
msgid ""
"`'existing-block'` — dragged from an existing block within a zone. Resolved "
"by either reordering within the zone (`arrayMove`) or moving to a different "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:122
msgid ""
"Zone droppable IDs use the prefix `zone-{zoneId}` so that `DocumentCanvas` "
"can distinguish a drop onto a zone (append to end) from a drop onto a "
"specific block (insert at position)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:126
msgid "TextBlockEditor and TipTap readonly sync"
