#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:1
msgid "Enhanced Validation & Semantic Detection"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:3
msgid ""
"This page covers the implementation of the chain validation engine and the "
"semantic link detection system. These two subsystems are tightly coupled — "
"the validation engine consumes the output of the semantic link query — so "
"they are documented together."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:7
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\enhanced-validation.md:7"
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:9
msgid ""
"ChainBuilder.tsx\n"
"  loads semantic links on mount via /v1/dmns/enhanced-chain-links\n"
"  on chain change → runValidation()\n"
"        │\n"
"        ▼\n"
"Validation Engine (inline in ChainBuilder.tsx)\n"
"  for each DMN in chain, for each input variable:\n"
"    check availableOutputs Set (exact identifier matches from prior steps)\n"
"    check semanticLinks array (semantic matches from prior steps)\n"
"    if neither → user must provide input\n"
"  determines:\n"
"    isDrdCompatible = no semantic matches used\n"
"    missingInputs = inputs requiring user input\n"
"        │\n"
"        ▼\n"
"Backend: findEnhancedChainLinks (sparql.service.ts)\n"
"  SPARQL query joining:\n"
"    Output Variables → Output Concepts → Shared Concepts\n"
"                                            ↑\n"
"    Input Variables  → Input Concepts  ────┘\n"
"  returns matchType: 'exact' | 'semantic' | 'both'"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:35
msgid "Backend SPARQL query"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:37
msgid ""
"The core of semantic detection is the `findEnhancedChainLinks` query. It "
"joins output and input variables through their SKOS concepts to find shared "
"concept URIs:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:39
msgid ""
"PREFIX cprmv: <https://cprmv.open-regels.nl/0.3.0/>\n"
"PREFIX cpsv:  <http://www.w3.org/ns/regorg#>\n"
"PREFIX dct:   <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>\n"
"PREFIX skos:  <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>\n"
"\n"
"SELECT ?dmn1Identifier ?dmn2Identifier\n"
"       ?outputVarId ?inputVarId\n"
"       ?variableType ?sharedConcept\n"
"       ?matchType\n"
"WHERE {\n"
"  # DMN1 produces an output variable\n"
"  ?outputVar a cpsv:Output ;\n"
"             cpsv:produces ?dmn1 ;\n"
"             dct:identifier ?outputVarId ;\n"
"             dct:type ?variableType .\n"
"\n"
"  # DMN2 requires an input variable of the same type\n"
"  ?inputVar a cpsv:Input ;\n"
"            cpsv:isRequiredBy ?dmn2 ;\n"
"            dct:identifier ?inputVarId ;\n"
"            dct:type ?variableType .\n"
"\n"
"  FILTER(?dmn1 != ?dmn2)\n"
"\n"
"  ?dmn1 a cprmv:DecisionModel ; dct:identifier ?dmn1Identifier .\n"
"  ?dmn2 a cprmv:DecisionModel ; dct:identifier ?dmn2Identifier .\n"
"\n"
"  # Check for semantic matching via shared concept\n"
"  OPTIONAL {\n"
"    ?outputConcept a skos:Concept ;\n"
"                   skos:exactMatch ?sharedConcept ;\n"
"                   dct:subject ?outputVar .\n"
"    ?inputConcept  a skos:Concept ;\n"
"                   skos:exactMatch ?sharedConcept ;\n"
"                   dct:subject ?inputVar .\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  BIND(\n"
"    IF(?outputVarId = ?inputVarId && BOUND(?sharedConcept), \"both\",\n"
"    IF(?outputVarId = ?inputVarId, \"exact\",\n"
"    IF(BOUND(?sharedConcept), \"semantic\", \"none\")))\n"
"    AS ?matchType\n"
"  )\n"
"\n"
"  FILTER(?matchType != \"none\")\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:88
msgid "**Critical requirements for correctness:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:90
msgid ""
"**Type compatibility** (`dct:type` must match) — prevents `Boolean` outputs "
"being linked to `Integer` inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:91
msgid ""
"**Shared concept** — both concepts must point to the **identical** third URI "
"via `skos:exactMatch`, not just any concept"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:92
msgid ""
"**`dct:subject` integrity** — the concept's `dct:subject` must correctly "
"point to the variable URI, not a DMN URI"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:94
msgid ""
"Post-query processing in `sparql.service.ts` expands `\"both\"` records into "
"two separate entries (one `\"exact\"`, one `\"semantic\"`), so the frontend "
"validation engine can process each match type independently:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:96
msgid ""
"if (matchType === 'both') {\n"
"  results.push({ ...link, matchType: 'exact' });\n"
"  results.push({ ...link, matchType: 'semantic' });\n"
"} else {\n"
"  results.push({ ...link, matchType });\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:107
msgid "Frontend validation engine"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:109
msgid ""
"`ChainBuilder.tsx` loads semantic links once on mount (or when the endpoint "
"changes) and stores them in `semanticLinks` state. On every chain change, "
"`runValidation()` evaluates the current chain:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:111
msgid ""
"const runValidation = () => {\n"
"  const availableOutputs = new Set<string>();\n"
"  const semanticMatches: SemanticMatch[] = [];\n"
"  const missingInputs: string[] = [];\n"
"  const drdIssues: string[] = [];\n"
"\n"
"  for (let i = 0; i < chain.length; i++) {\n"
"    const dmn = chain[i];\n"
"    const prevDmn = chain[i - 1];\n"
"\n"
"    for (const input of dmn.inputs) {\n"
"      // Exact match\n"
"      if (availableOutputs.has(input.identifier)) continue;\n"
"\n"
"      // Semantic match\n"
"      const semanticLink = semanticLinks.find(\n"
"        link =>\n"
"          link.dmn2.identifier === dmn.identifier &&\n"
"          link.dmn1.identifier === prevDmn?.identifier &&\n"
"          link.inputVariable === input.identifier &&\n"
"          link.matchType === 'semantic'\n"
"      );\n"
"\n"
"      if (semanticLink) {\n"
"        semanticMatches.push({ ... });\n"
"        drdIssues.push(`'${input.identifier}' requires semantic match`);\n"
"        continue;\n"
"      }\n"
"\n"
"      // User must supply\n"
"      missingInputs.push(input.identifier);\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    // Add this DMN's outputs to the available set\n"
"    for (const output of dmn.outputs) {\n"
"      availableOutputs.add(output.identifier);\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  const isDrdCompatible = drdIssues.length === 0;\n"
"  setValidationResult({ isDrdCompatible, semanticMatches, missingInputs });\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:156
msgid ""
"The `isDrdCompatible` flag controls which save path is offered — \"Save as "
"DRD\" or \"Save as Sequential Template\" — and whether the DRD deployment "
"flow is triggered."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:160
msgid "React state dependency tracking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:162
msgid ""
"`runValidation` has a `useEffect` dependency on `[chain, userInputs, "
"semanticLinks]`. The `semanticLinks` dependency is intentional: when the "
"endpoint changes and new links load, validation re-runs even if the chain "
"hasn't changed. This ensures the validation state always reflects the "
"current endpoint's concept graph."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:166
msgid "Debugging notes"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:168
msgid ""
"During development, a common failure mode was that semantic chains appeared "
"to have zero semantic links despite correct SPARQL syntax. The root causes "
"discovered through debugging were:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:170
msgid ""
"**`dct:subject` pointing to the DMN URI instead of the variable URI** — the "
"CPSV Editor at one point generated concepts with `dct:subject <.../dmn>` "
"instead of `dct:subject <.../dmn/output/1>`. The SPARQL join then silently "
"returned nothing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:171
msgid ""
"**Mismatched `dct:type` values** — `\"Boolean\"` from one agency and "
"`\"boolean\"` (lowercase) from another prevented the type filter from "
"matching. RDF datatype URIs are case-sensitive."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:172
msgid ""
"**`skos:exactMatch` pointing to the concept's own URI** — a circular "
"reference that produces no shared concept."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cenhanced-validation.md:174
msgid ""
"The validation console logs (`[Validation] ✓ DRD | X missing | 0 semantic` "
"and `[SemanticLinks] ✓ Loaded 26 links (16 semantic)`) were added to make "
"these failure modes visible during QA."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:1
msgid "Form Editor Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:3
msgid ""
"The Form Editor wraps the `@bpmn-io/form-js` library in a two-panel React "
"component. This page covers the component structure, storage layer, and the "
"integration points with the BPMN Modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:7
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\form-editor.md:7"
msgid "Component structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:9
msgid ""
"packages/frontend/src/components/FormEditor/\n"
"├── FormEditor.tsx        main orchestrator — state, seeding, CRUD "
"callbacks\n"
"├── FormCanvas.tsx        @bpmn-io/form-js editor canvas wrapper\n"
"└── FormList.tsx          left-panel list with create / rename / delete "
"actions\n"
"\n"
"packages/frontend/src/\n"
"├── services/\n"
"│   └── formService.ts    localStorage CRUD for FormSchema records\n"
"└── types/\n"
"    └── index.ts          FormSchema interface"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:24
msgid "`FormSchema` type"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:26
msgid ""
"interface FormSchema {\n"
"  id: string;                          // internal UUID used as list key\n"
"  name: string;                        // display name\n"
"  description?: string;\n"
"  schema: Record<string, unknown>;     // the @bpmn-io/form-js JSON schema\n"
"  createdAt: string;                   // ISO 8601\n"
"  updatedAt: string;\n"
"  readonly?: boolean;                  // true for EXAMPLE seed forms\n"
"  status?: 'example' | 'wip';\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:39
msgid ""
"The `schema.id` field inside the JSON schema object is the **form "
"identifier** used in BPMN XML (`camunda:formRef`) and in the Operaton "
"deployment. It is distinct from the outer `FormSchema.id` used as the "
"localStorage record key."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:43
msgid "`FormService`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:45
msgid ""
"`FormService` is a static class providing synchronous localStorage CRUD:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:47
msgid ""
"import { FormService } from '../../services/formService';\n"
"\n"
"const STORAGE_KEY = 'linkedDataExplorer_formSchemas';\n"
"\n"
"FormService.getForms(): FormSchema[]\n"
"FormService.getForm(formId: string): FormSchema | null   // by "
"FormSchema.id\n"
"FormService.saveForm(form: FormSchema): void             // upsert by .id\n"
"FormService.deleteForm(formId: string): void"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:58
msgid ""
"The methods read/write the entire array on each call. There is no batching "
"or indexedDB fallback — the storage size is small (three seed schemas are ≈ "
"3 KB total)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:62
msgid "`FormEditor.tsx` — seeding logic"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:64
msgid ""
"On mount, `FormEditor.tsx` runs a `useEffect` that checks for the presence "
"of each seed form by `FormSchema.id`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:66
msgid ""
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"  const existing = FormService.getForms();\n"
"  const existingIds = new Set(existing.map((f) => f.id));\n"
"\n"
"  for (const seed of SEED_FORMS) {\n"
"    if (!existingIds.has(seed.id)) {\n"
"      FormService.saveForm(seed);\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  setForms(FormService.getForms());\n"
"}, []);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:81
msgid ""
"The three seed IDs are `example_kapvergunning_start`, "
"`example_tree_felling_review`, and `example_awb_notify_applicant`. Their "
"`readonly: true` flag causes `FormList` to suppress rename and delete "
"controls."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:83
msgid ""
"The `schema.id` values embedded in the JSON schemas are `kapvergunning-"
"start`, `tree-felling-review`, and `awb-notify-applicant` respectively — "
"these are the values written into `camunda:formRef`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:87
msgid "`FormCanvas.tsx` — editor lifecycle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:89
msgid "`FormCanvas.tsx` mounts a `@bpmn-io/form-js` `FormEditor` instance:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:91
msgid ""
"import { FormEditor as FormJsEditor } from '@bpmn-io/form-js';\n"
"\n"
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"  const editor = new FormJsEditor({ container: containerRef.current });\n"
"  editorRef.current = editor;\n"
"\n"
"  editor.importSchema(schema);\n"
"  editor.on('changed', () => setHasChanges(true));\n"
"\n"
"  return () => {\n"
"    editor.destroy();\n"
"    editorRef.current = null;\n"
"  };\n"
"}, [schema]);   // re-mounts on schema identity change (new form selected)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:108
msgid ""
"The `schema` prop is the `FormSchema.schema` object for the currently active "
"form. Because `schema` is a new object reference each time a different form "
"is selected, the `useEffect` re-runs and the editor instance is replaced "
"cleanly."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:110
msgid "Save flow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:112
msgid ""
"const handleSave = async () => {\n"
"  const { schema: savedSchema } = await editorRef.current.saveSchema();\n"
"  onSave(savedSchema);   // parent writes to FormService\n"
"  setHasChanges(false);\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:120
msgid "Export flow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:122
msgid ""
"const handleExport = async () => {\n"
"  const { schema: exportSchema } = await editorRef.current.saveSchema();\n"
"  const formId = exportSchema.id ?? 'form';\n"
"  // ... download as `{formId}.form`\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:132
msgid "Integration with `FormTemplateSelector`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:134
msgid ""
"`FormTemplateSelector` (in `BpmnModeler/`) reads forms directly from "
"`FormService.getForms()` on mount. Because both `FormEditor` and "
"`FormTemplateSelector` use the same `FormService` singleton over shared "
"`localStorage`, no pub/sub or context is needed — a form saved in the Form "
"Editor is immediately visible the next time the properties panel mounts for "
"a `UserTask` or `StartEvent`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:138
msgid "Form schema requirements for Operaton"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:140
msgid "Every form deployed to Operaton must satisfy:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:142
msgid "`schemaVersion: 16` — the version Operaton resolves at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:143
msgid "A `schema.id` that matches the `camunda:formRef` value in the BPMN XML."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:144
msgid ""
"A `Button` component with `action: \"submit\"` at the end of the "
"`components` array. `@bpmn-io/form-js` does not inject one automatically; "
"omitting it causes the form to render but never emit the `submit` event."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:145
msgid ""
"Deployed in the **same Operaton deployment** as the BPMN that references it. "
"The deploy modal in the BPMN Modeler handles this automatically — see [BPMN "
"Modeler Implementation — Deploy modal]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:149
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\form-editor.md:149"
msgid "CSS"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cform-editor.md:151
