#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cropa-records.md:259
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\ropa-records.md:259"
msgid "Type safety — DB row types and mappers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cropa-records.md:261
msgid ""
"`ropa.service.ts` follows the same three-layer DB type pattern used by "
"`assets.service.ts`. Row types `RopaRecordRow` and `RopaFieldRow` in `src/db/"
"types.ts` mirror the exact column names and pg-native types of "
"`ropa_records` and `ropa_personal_data_fields`. The mapper functions "
"`mapRopaRecord` and `mapRopaField` in `src/db/mappers.ts` perform all "
"snake_case → camelCase conversion, `null` → `undefined` coercion, and `Date` "
"→ ISO string serialisation in one place. Services use "
"`pool.query<RopaRecordRow>()` — no `as` casts appear in query results."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cropa-records.md:263
msgid ""
"RoPA types live in `src/types/ropa.types.ts` rather than `src/domain/"
"types.ts` because they are mirrored on the frontend at `packages/frontend/"
"src/types/ropa.types.ts`. The pattern is otherwise identical."
msgstr ""

