#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:143
msgid "One-click deploy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:145
msgid ""
"The **Deploy** button in the Modeler toolbar opens a deploy modal that "
"collects all resources needed for a complete Operaton deployment:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:147
msgid "The currently open BPMN file"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:148
msgid ""
"Any subprocess BPMNs referenced via `calledElement` attributes (resolved "
"recursively from saved processes)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:149
msgid ""
"All `.form` files whose `id` matches a `camunda:formRef` found anywhere in "
"the bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:156
msgid ""
"All resources are sent in a single multipart `POST` to Operaton. Because the "
"BPMN and its forms share one deployment ID, `camunda:formRef` resolves "
"correctly at runtime — no separate form deployment step is needed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:158
msgid "The modal provides:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:160
msgid ""
"**Operaton endpoint** — pre-filled from `VITE_OPERATON_BASE_URL`, editable "
"per deployment"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:161
msgid ""
"**Username / Password** — optional HTTP Basic Auth for instances that "
"require it"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:162
msgid ""
"**Resource list** — shows exactly what will be included before you commit"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:163
msgid ""
"**Deploy button** — disabled after a successful deployment to prevent "
"accidental re-deploy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:165
msgid ""
"If a `camunda:formRef` references a form ID that is not found in "
"`localStorage`, it is listed as an unmatched reference. The deployment still "
"proceeds, but that form will not resolve at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:169
msgid "RoPA record linkage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:171
msgid ""
"Every process in the LDE can be linked to a RoPA record via `ronl:ropaRef`. "
"Two mechanisms are available:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:173
msgid ""
"**RoPA Record selector in the process list** — when a process is open, a "
"**RoPA Record** panel is pinned to the bottom of the left panel below the "
"scrollable process list. A dropdown shows all available records; selecting "
"one writes `ronl:ropaRef` into the process XML immediately."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:175
msgid ""
"**BPMN Link tab in the RoPA Editor** — the RoPA Editor's BPMN Link tab "
"writes the same attribute and shows whether the current record ID matches "
"the value already in the XML."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:177
msgid ""
"Both mechanisms produce identical results. The attribute is registered in "
"`ronlModdleDescriptor.json` under the `http://ronl.nl/schema/1.0` namespace "
"so it survives `saveXML()` serialisation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:179
msgid "Deploy warning"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:181
msgid ""
"The deploy modal checks for the presence of `ronl:ropaRef` on the process "
"element. If absent, an amber warning appears between the resource list and "
"the resource count line. The warning is non-blocking — the bundle can still "
"be deployed — but is intended to prevent deploying to production without a "
"linked RoPA record."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:183
msgid "See [RoPA Records]{1} for the full feature description."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:187
msgid "DSO activiteit linkage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:189
msgid ""
"The BPMN Modeler footer panel includes a **DSO Activity** selector for "
"linking a process to a DSO activiteit URN. Pasting a URN and clicking "
"**Verify** queries the live DSO RTR; on success the panel shows the "
"activity's omschrijving, authority block, and a link to the public RTR "
"viewer. The URN is persisted on `<bpmn:process>` as the "
"`ronl:dsoActiviteitUrn` attribute and survives `saveXML` round-trips."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:191
msgid ""
"See [DSO Integration]{1} for the full integration overview and [DSO Explorer "
"user guide]{2} for the verification workflow."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:195
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\features\\bpmn-modeler.md:195"
msgid "Language and organization"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:197
msgid "The footer panel includes **Language** and **Organization** selectors:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:199
msgid ""
"**Language** — ISO 639-1 dropdown (Language-agnostic / English / Dutch / "
"German). Persisted as `ronl:language` on `<bpmn:process>` and as the "
"`process_definitions.language` DB column."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:200
msgid ""
"**Organization** — free-text input with autocomplete from existing "
"organization keys. Persisted as `ronl:organization` and as the DB column."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:202
msgid ""
"Both fields are pending-until-Save: typing in them updates the editor's "
"draft state but does not regroup the artefact in the list panel until "
"**Save** is clicked. Saving a shell process atomically propagates `language` "
"and `organization` to all linked subprocesses."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:204
msgid ""
"The list panel toolbar offers a language filter and a search box; cards are "
"grouped under collapsible organization headers. Subprocesses follow their "
"shell's organization regardless of their own tag."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:206
msgid ""
"See [Multilingualism]{1} for the full feature description and "
"[Multilingualism user guide]{2} for the tagging workflow."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:210
msgid "Deploy modal — language consistency check"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:212
msgid ""
"When the deploy modal opens, LDE walks the bundle resources (shell BPMN + "
"subprocess BPMNs + linked forms + linked documents) and collects all "
"distinct language tags. If more than one is present, an amber warning "
"surfaces inline in the modal listing the offending codes. The warning is non-"
"blocking — Deploy stays enabled. DMNs are excluded from the check (language-"
"agnostic by design)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:214
msgid ""
"The check sits alongside the existing RoPA-missing warning, both rendered "
"between the resource list and the resource count."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:218
msgid "Tree Felling Permit example"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:220
msgid ""
"On first launch, the Modeler auto-creates the **Tree Felling Permit** "
"example process, demonstrating a complete municipal workflow: application "
"submission, two `BusinessRuleTask` elements linked to DMN decision models "
"(`TreeFellingDecision`, `ReplacementTreeDecision`), an exclusive gateway "
"routing to permit granted or rejected outcomes. The example is protected "
"from deletion and serves as a reference for process designers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:224
msgid "Engine compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:226
msgid ""
"The Modeler targets Operaton, the open-source fork of Camunda 7 CE. It uses "
"`camunda-bpmn-moddle` for namespace support since no `operaton-bpmn-moddle` "
"package exists yet. Operaton accepts both `camunda:` and `operaton:` "
"namespace attributes, ensuring compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:228
msgid ""
"The Modeler targets Operaton, the open-source fork of Camunda 7 CE. It uses "
"`camunda-bpmn-moddle` for namespace support since no `operaton-bpmn-moddle` "
"package exists yet. The `camunda:formRef` and `camunda:formRefBinding` "
"attributes used for form linking are also accepted by Operaton under the "
"`camunda:` namespace."
msgstr ""

