#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:1
msgid "DMN Discovery & Chain Building"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:3
msgid ""
"The Chain Builder is the central feature of the Linked Data Explorer. It "
"queries the active TriplyDB endpoint for all published DMN decision models, "
"displays them with their input and output variables, and lets you compose "
"them into executable chains."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:12
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\features\\dmn-chain-building.md:12"
msgid "DMN discovery"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:14
msgid ""
"When you open the Chain Builder, it queries TriplyDB using the CPRMV "
"vocabulary to find all published `cprmv:DecisionModel` resources. Each model "
"appears as a card in the **Available DMNs** panel showing its title, "
"identifier, variable counts, and publishing organisation. A real-time search "
"field filters the list by title or identifier."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:16
msgid ""
"Expanding a card reveals its full variable list: input variables in blue, "
"output variables in green, each with its name, identifier, and datatype "
"(`Integer`, `String`, `Boolean`, `Date`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:20
msgid "Chain composition"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:22
msgid ""
"Drag a DMN card from the Available DMNs panel into the **Chain Composer** to "
"add it to your chain. Cards stack vertically in execution order. The "
"composer evaluates variable compatibility in real time:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:24
msgid ""
"If an output variable of the preceding DMN matches the input identifier of "
"the next DMN exactly, the connection is **DRD-compatible** — the chain can "
"be saved as a unified Decision Requirements Diagram."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:25
msgid ""
"If the match is only via `skos:exactMatch` semantic concepts, the chain is "
"**sequential** — it will execute as a series of individual API calls with "
"runtime variable mapping."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:26
msgid ""
"If a required input has neither an exact nor a semantic match from earlier "
"in the chain, the user must provide it manually in the input form."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:28
msgid ""
"The validation panel below the composer shows the current status and lists "
"any missing inputs or semantic matches."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-chain-building.md:32
msgid "Validation states"
msgstr ""

