msgid "DRD Generation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:3
msgid ""
"When all variable connections in a chain are exact identifier matches, the "
"chain can be saved as a **Decision Requirements Diagram (DRD)** — a single, "
"unified DMN artifact deployed to Operaton. This replaces multiple sequential "
"API calls with one call that evaluates the entire chain internally."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:12
msgid "Why DRDs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:14
msgid ""
"Sequential chain execution makes one API call per DMN in the chain. A three-"
"step chain makes three calls. A DRD makes one call regardless of chain "
"length, with Operaton handling the internal decision flow via "
"`<informationRequirement>` wiring in the DMN XML. The performance "
"improvement is approximately 50% for a two-step chain and grows with chain "
"length."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:16
msgid ""
"DRDs also carry semantic integrity: the `<informationRequirement>` elements "
"correctly express that one decision depends on the output of another, which "
"is the proper DMN 1.3 way to model decision dependencies rather than "
"treating them as independent steps."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:20
msgid "Reusability"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:22
msgid ""
"A saved DRD template appears in **My Templates** with a purple 🔗 DRD badge. "
"It can be loaded and executed just like any other chain, but with a single "
"API call. DRD templates also appear in the BPMN Modeler's [Link to DMN/DRD]"
"{1} dropdown, grouped separately from single DMNs, so process designers can "
"reference the entire chain from a `BusinessRuleTask` element."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:26
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:28
msgid ""
"Chains with semantic (non-exact) variable connections cannot be saved as "
"DRDs. The validation system explicitly blocks the DRD save path for such "
"chains. See [Semantic Analysis]{1} for why."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:29
msgid ""
"DRD templates are stored in browser `localStorage` in Phase 1. A database "
"migration is planned for Phase 2."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdrd-generation.md:30
msgid "Export and versioning of DRD XML is planned for Phase 2."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:1
msgid "DSO Integration — Phase Plan & Test Guidance"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:3
msgid "End goal"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:5
msgid ""
"A **DSO-driven AWB process bundle**: given a location and a werkzaamheid, "
"LDE produces a deployable Operaton package — BPMN subprocess + DMN + form "
"schema + document template — all seeded from authoritative DSO source data "
"rather than authored by hand."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:9
msgid "The data flow that makes this possible"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:11
msgid ""
"Werkzaamheid (what someone wants to do)\n"
"    ↓  linked to\n"
"Activiteit (the legal activity at that location)\n"
"    ↓  has\n"
"Regelbeheerobjecten\n"
"    ├── indieningsvereisten  →  STTR file → Form fields (what must be "
"submitted)\n"
"    ├── conclusie            →  STTR file → DMN decision model (what the "
"authority decides)\n"
"    └── maatregelen          →  STTR file → Document template (conditions in "
"the beschikking)\n"
"    ↓  governed by\n"
"BPMN subprocess (the AWB procedural shell wrapping all of the above)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:24
msgid "The `functioneleStructuurRef` is the pivot"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:26
msgid ""
"Every regelBeheerobject on an activity carries a `functioneleStructuurRef`. "
"This reference links the RTR activity taxonomy to the actual applicable rule "
"files (STTR) in the Uitvoeren Gegevens API. The Zoekinterface returns it "
"directly alongside each werkzaamheid result — visible in the Works tab as "
"the `ref:` line on each row. The Activity Detail panel shows rule types "
"present; the `functioneleStructuurRef` per rule type is returned by the RTR "
"detail call and is the input to Step 1 of the next cycle."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:28
msgid "The `functioneleStructuurRef` is a full concept URI. Two formats exist:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:30
msgid ""
"**Zoekinterface** (werkzaamheid-level): `http://toepasbare-"
"regels.omgevingswet.overheid.nl/werkzaamheden/id/concept/GebouwPlaatsen`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:31
msgid ""
"**RTR detail** (regelBeheerobject-level): `http://toepasbare-"
"regels.omgevingswet.overheid.nl/00000001005024249000/id/concept/"
"Conclusienl.imow-gm0995.activiteit.a42ec23b8e4d464b8d32a1e88ac6d4cd`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration-phase-plan.md:33
msgid ""
"Both are passed to `GET /toepasbareRegels?functioneleStructuurRef=...` in "
"Phase 4 — the authority-scoped format from the RTR detail is the more "
"precise one."
msgstr ""

