msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:5
msgid ""
"LDE supports tagging design artefacts (BPMN processes, Camunda forms, "
"document templates) with a **language** and an **organization** so that "
"bundles can be designed once and deployed in multiple languages without "
"forking the underlying logic."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:7
msgid ""
"The model is sibling-artefact i18n, not in-schema key-lookup i18n: each form/"
"BPMN/document exists once per language, with a language tag, and the deploy "
"modal warns if a bundle mixes languages. DMNs stay language-agnostic — "
"variable keys remain stable English across language siblings, so a single "
"DMN serves both English and Dutch versions of the BPMN that calls it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:9
msgid ""
"The LDE interface itself remains English. Language tags apply only to the "
"design artefacts the LDE produces."
msgstr ""

