#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:87
msgid "Deploying the bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:94
msgid ""
"Open `RipPhase1Process.bpmn` in the BPMN Modeler and click **Deploy**. The "
"modal resolves all `camunda:formRef` and `ronl:documentRef` attributes "
"automatically and lists all 12 resources. Click **Deploy to Operaton** to "
"deploy."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:96
msgid ""
"!!! tip Set a Business Key equal to the project number when starting the "
"process from the Operaton Cockpit. This makes process instances easy to find "
"by project number."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:101
msgid "Starting the process"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:103
msgid ""
"The process is designed to be started from the Human Tasks interface in "
"MijnOmgeving (or the Operaton Tasklist), not directly from the Cockpit. "
"Starting from the Cockpit's generic start dialog is possible for testing — "
"click **Start** and the first user task (`Complete intake form`) will appear "
"in the task list immediately."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:105
msgid ""
"!!! note `candidateGroups` is set to `infra-projectteam` for all tasks by "
"the DMN. Any user with this group membership can claim tasks."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:110
msgid "eDOCS integration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:112
msgid ""
"The three ServiceTasks in the process write documents to the project "
"workspace in eDOCS. In stub mode (`EDOCS_STUB_MODE=true`), the external task "
"worker returns realistic fake responses and logs all calls. No code changes "
"are needed when switching to a live eDOCS server — set "
"`EDOCS_STUB_MODE=false` and provide the real credentials."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:114
msgid "See [eDOCS Integration]{1} for setup and configuration."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\features\\ropa-records.md:1"
msgid "RoPA Records"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:3
msgid ""
"The RoPA Records feature lets Product Owners author and maintain a **Record "
"of Processing Activities** (RoPA) for every deployed process bundle, "
"fulfilling the mandatory GDPR Article 30 obligation for government "
"processing activities. Records are stored in PostgreSQL, linked to their "
"BPMN process via `ronl:ropaRef`, and published to a public-facing website "
"isolated from the LDE stack."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:12
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\features\\ropa-records.md:12"
msgid "Two-panel layout"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:14
msgid ""
"The RoPA Records view follows the same two-panel convention as the Form "
"Editor:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:16
msgid ""
"**Left panel** — Record list. All RoPA records grouped as shell processes "
"first, subprocesses second, each with a DRAFT / ACTIVE / ARCHIVED status "
"badge and a delete control."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:17
msgid ""
"**Right panel** — Record editor. Four tabs covering the full GDPR Art. 30 "
"data model, BPMN linkage, and lifecycle management."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:21
msgid "Record list"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:23
msgid ""
"Each entry in the list shows the record title, the `bpmnProcessId` it "
"covers, and its current status. Shell records are top-level entries; "
"subprocess records are indented beneath their parent shell with a tree "
"connector — mirroring the hierarchy in the BPMN Modeler process list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:30
msgid ""
"Clicking a record opens it in the editor. The **+** button in the panel "
"header creates a new blank record."
msgstr ""

