#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:1
msgid "Operaton DMN Compatibility Checklist"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:3
msgid ""
"A practical checklist for authoring DMN files that deploy and execute "
"correctly in Operaton (the open-source Camunda 7 CE fork). Work through this "
"list when a DMN fails to deploy or produces unexpected results."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:7
msgid "1) Namespace and DMN version"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:9
msgid ""
"✅ Use DMN 1.3 namespace: `xmlns=\"https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20191111/"
"MODEL/\"`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:10
msgid ""
"✅ Avoid DMN 1.1 namespace — Operaton supports 1.1 but behaviour may differ "
"for newer features"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:11
msgid ""
"✅ Verify `<definitions>` has a valid `namespace` attribute and a unique `id`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:15
msgid "2) Decision IDs and references"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:17
msgid "✅ Every `<decision>` element must have a unique `id` attribute"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:18
msgid ""
"✅ `<requiredDecision href=\"#...\">` must reference the `id` of another "
"`<decision>` in the same `<definitions>`, not its `name`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:19
msgid ""
"✅ `<informationRequirement>` elements need their own unique `id` attribute"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:20
msgid ""
"✅ Avoid duplicate `id` values anywhere in the document — even across "
"`<dmndi:DMNDI>` elements"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:24
msgid "3) FEEL expressions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:26
msgid ""
"✅ Use `not(x)` — **not** `not x` (the latter is a unary test, not a "
"negation function)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:27
msgid ""
"✅ Unary test intervals: `[a..b)`, `(a..b]`, `[a..b]` — parentheses for "
"exclusive bounds"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:28
msgid ""
"✅ `and` / `or` in unary tests refer to multiple unary conditions on the "
"same input — do not use them as Boolean operators in FEEL expressions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:29
msgid "✅ String literals must use double quotes: `\"active\"`, not `'active'`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:30
msgid "✅ Date literals: `date(\"2026-01-01\")`, not bare strings"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:31
msgid ""
"✅ Test FEEL expressions in isolation with the Operaton REST API `evaluate` "
"endpoint before deploying a full DRD"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:35
msgid "4) Variable naming and types"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:37
msgid ""
"✅ Use simple variable names (letters, digits, underscore). Avoid spaces and "
"punctuation in variable names referenced by FEEL."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:38
msgid ""
"✅ In FEEL, reference **runtime variables** (the `<variable name=\"...\">`) "
"rather than element IDs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:39
msgid ""
"✅ Keep numeric types consistent — `Integer` vs `Double` differences between "
"request and DMN declaration cause runtime type errors"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:43
msgid "5) Null / missing inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:45
msgid ""
"If a required input may be absent, Operaton may throw a runtime error rather "
"than producing a null output."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:47
msgid ""
"✅ Use null-safe FEEL where inputs may be missing: `x = false` is safer than "
"`not(x)` when `x` can be null"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:48
msgid "✅ Use `if x = null then … else …` for optional inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:49
msgid ""
"✅ For optional inputs, provide defaults in FEEL expressions: `if "
"medischeVerklaring = true then true else missendeMaand = false`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:53
msgid "6) DMNDI (diagram section)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:55
msgid ""
"The engine ignores the `<dmndi:DMNDI>` block for execution, but the Operaton "
"Modeler and UI use it for rendering."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:57
msgid "✅ Avoid multiple DI elements referencing the same `dmnElementRef`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:58
msgid ""
"✅ `<dmndi:DMNEdge>` `dmnElementRef` must reference an "
"`<informationRequirement>` ID, not a `<decision>` ID"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:59
msgid ""
"✅ If deployment fails and you cannot isolate the cause, temporarily remove "
"the entire `<dmndi:DMNDI>…</dmndi:DMNDI>` block, deploy without it, and re-"
"add once the execution logic is confirmed working"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:63
msgid "7) Operaton-specific extensions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:65
msgid ""
"✅ If Operaton enforces history cleanup TTL, set "
"`camunda:historyTimeToLive=\"...\"` on `<decision>` elements (or configure a "
"global default in the engine)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:66
msgid ""
"✅ Keep extension namespaces consistent: `xmlns:camunda=\"http://camunda.org/"
"schema/1.0/dmn\"`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:70
msgid "8) Deployment debugging workflow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:72
msgid "If you see `ENGINE-22004 Unable to transform DMN resource …`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:74
msgid "Verify DMN namespace and version (DMN 1.1 vs 1.3)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:75
msgid ""
"Check for broken `href=\"#...\"` references — the target `id` must exist"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:76
msgid ""
"Check FEEL parsing: `not x` vs `not(x)`, unary test `and/or` vs Boolean `and/"
"or`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:77
msgid "Temporarily remove `<dmndi:DMNDI>` to rule it out"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:78
msgid ""
"Inspect Operaton server logs immediately after `ENGINE-22004` for the "
"underlying parse error — the 22004 message is a wrapper; the actual cause is "
"one line below it"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:82
msgid "9) Testing strategy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:84
msgid ""
"✅ Test leaf decisions first (single-input literal expressions) before "
"testing a full DRD"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:85
msgid ""
"✅ When testing a decision that depends on others, provide the full upstream "
"input set — unless you have made all inputs null-safe"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Coperaton-dmn-compatibility.md:86
msgid ""
"✅ Maintain one \"superset\" JSON payload covering all possible inputs for "
"the chain, usable for quick regression testing across DMN versions"
msgstr ""

