msgid "BPMN Modeler"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:3
msgid ""
"The BPMN Modeler lets you design government service workflows and link "
"decision model references directly to DMNs and DRDs you have discovered or "
"saved in the Chain Builder."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:7
msgid "Opening the Modeler"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:9
msgid ""
"Click the Workflow icon in the left sidebar. The Modeler opens with the "
"process list on the left, the canvas in the centre, and the properties panel "
"on the right."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:11
msgid ""
"On your first visit, the **Tree Felling Permit** example process loads "
"automatically. It demonstrates a complete municipal workflow and serves as a "
"reference — examine it before creating your own processes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:15
msgid "Creating a process"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:17
msgid "Click the blue **+** button at the top of the process list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:18
msgid ""
"A new process named \"New Process\" appears in the list and the canvas shows "
"an empty diagram with a start event."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:19
msgid "Double-click the process name in the list to rename it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:23
msgid "Building a diagram"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:25
msgid ""
"Drag elements from the palette on the left edge of the canvas onto the "
"diagram area. Connect elements by clicking the source element and dragging "
"the blue arrow handle that appears on hover to the target element."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:27
msgid ""
"Available element types: start events, intermediate events, end events, "
"tasks (user, service, business rule), gateways (exclusive, parallel, "
"inclusive, event-based), sub-processes, data objects, pools, and text "
"annotations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:31
msgid "Linking a BusinessRuleTask to a decision"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:33
msgid ""
"Select a **BusinessRuleTask** on the canvas. The properties panel on the "
"right shows the element details, including a **DMN/DRD Decision Reference** "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:40
msgid "Click **Link to DMN/DRD** to open the dropdown."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:41
msgid "The dropdown shows two groups:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:41
msgid ""
"**🔗 DRDs (Unified Chains)** — DRD templates saved from the Chain Builder"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:41
msgid ""
"**📋 Single DMNs** — individual decision models from the active TriplyDB "
"endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:44
msgid ""
"Select an option. The `camunda:decisionRef` field auto-populates with the "
"correct identifier and a suggested `camunda:resultVariable` value appears."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:45
msgid ""
"An info card confirms your selection. DRD cards show the constituent DMNs "
"the DRD combines; single DMN cards show the decision identifier."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:49
msgid "Linking a UserTask or StartEvent to a form"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:51
msgid ""
"`UserTask` and `StartEvent` elements can be linked to Camunda Forms authored "
"in the [Form Editor]{1}. Once linked, Operaton renders the form at runtime "
"for the citizen or caseworker assigned to that task."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:53
msgid ""
"Select a **UserTask** or **StartEvent** on the canvas. The properties panel "
"shows a **Link to Form** section beneath the standard element fields."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:60
msgid ""
"Click the **Link to Form** dropdown. It lists all forms currently saved in "
"the Form Editor."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:61
msgid "Select the form you want to link."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:62
msgid ""
"A confirmation card appears below the dropdown showing the form name and the "
"resulting `camunda:formRef` value."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:63
msgid ""
"A **green badge** appears below the element on the canvas, confirming the "
"link."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:65
msgid ""
"The dropdown writes `camunda:formRef` and "
"`camunda:formRefBinding=\"latest\"` into the BPMN XML. `binding: latest` "
"means Operaton always uses the most recently deployed version of that form — "
"you do not need to pin a specific version."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:67
msgid ""
"To unlink a form, open the dropdown and select the blank option at the top."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:69
msgid ""
"!!! tip \"Form not in the list?\" Open the **Form Editor** view and create "
"or save the form first. Forms appear in the dropdown immediately after "
"saving — no page reload required."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:74
msgid "Deploying to Operaton"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:76
msgid ""
"The Modeler can deploy your process — including subprocess BPMNs and linked "
"forms — to Operaton in a single step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:78
msgid ""
"Click the **Deploy** button in the canvas toolbar. The deploy modal opens "
"and lists:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:80
msgid "The current BPMN file"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:81
msgid ""
"Any subprocess BPMNs it calls via `calledElement` (resolved from your saved "
"processes)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:82
msgid ""
"All `.form` files whose IDs match `camunda:formRef` references in the bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:83
msgid ""
"All `.document` files whose IDs match `ronl:documentRef` references in the "
"bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:85
msgid ""
"!!! note \"DMNs are not part of the deploy bundle\" Decision models "
"referenced via `camunda:decisionRef` on `BusinessRuleTask` elements are "
"**not** included in this deployment. DMNs reach Operaton through a separate "
"path: they are published to TriplyDB by the [CPSV Editor]{1} and deployed to "
"Operaton from there. The BPMN process resolves `camunda:decisionRef` at "
"runtime against whatever is already deployed — as long as the DMN key "
"matches, no additional action is needed here."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:93
msgid ""
"Review the resource list. If a referenced form ID is shown as unmatched, "
"open the Form Editor and save a form with that ID before deploying."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:94
msgid ""
"Confirm or edit the **Operaton endpoint** URL. It is pre-filled from the "
"environment configuration."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:95
msgid ""
"If your Operaton instance requires authentication, enter the **Username** "
"and **Password**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:96
msgid "Click **Deploy**. All resources are sent in one multipart request."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:97
msgid ""
"On success, a deployment ID is shown and the Deploy button is disabled to "
"prevent accidental re-deploy."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:99
msgid ""
"Because the BPMN and all its forms land in the same Operaton deployment, "
"`camunda:formRef` resolves correctly at runtime with no additional steps."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:103
msgid "Editing element properties"
