msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:146
msgid "AWB shell and subprocess examples"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:148
msgid ""
"The process library ships with two AWB shell processes and their "
"subprocesses:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:150
msgid ""
"**AWB Generic Process** (`SHELL`) — the universal eight-phase AWB procedural "
"shell for the Kapvergunning (tree felling permit). Calls "
"`TreeFellingPermitSubProcess` via a Call Activity at Phase 4+5."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:152
msgid ""
"└── **Tree Felling Permit** (`SUB`) — evaluates the substantive tree felling "
"decision and routes to caseworker review."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:154
msgid ""
"**AWB Zorgtoeslag — Provisional Entitlement** (`SHELL`) — AWB shell wired "
"for the Zorgtoeslag provisional entitlement subprocess."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:156
msgid ""
"└── **Zorgtoeslag — Provisional Entitlement** (`SUB`) — validates "
"application, retrieves income data, evaluates the `resultaat_zorgtoeslag` "
"DMN, and routes to caseworker review."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:158
msgid ""
"└── **Zorgtoeslag — Final Settlement** (`SUB`) — started via the "
"`FinalIncomeReceived` message event once final annual income data arrives "
"from Belastingdienst. Evaluates confirmed income and sets the settlement "
"outcome."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:160
msgid ""
"All example processes are protected (`EXAMPLE` badge, delete disabled). To "
"use one as a starting point, export it and import the copy as a new process."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:1
msgid "Building DMN Chains"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide covers the complete chain-building workflow, from discovering "
"DMNs to executing a chain and interpreting results."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:7
msgid "Opening the Chain Builder"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:9
msgid ""
"Click the GitBranch icon in the left sidebar. The view loads three panels: "
"Available DMNs (left), Chain Composer (centre), Configuration (right)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:11
msgid ""
"On first load, the backend queries TriplyDB for all published DMN models. "
"The Available DMNs panel populates within a few seconds. If it remains "
"empty, check the active endpoint in the Configuration panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:15
msgid "Inspecting DMNs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:17
msgid ""
"Each DMN card in the Available DMNs panel shows its title, identifier, "
"variable counts, publishing organisation, and any governance badge. Click on "
"a card to expand it and see the full variable list — inputs in blue, outputs "
"in green, each with its identifier and datatype."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:19
msgid ""
"Before building a chain, identify which DMNs you want to connect and verify "
"that the output variables of the first match the input variables of the "
"second, either by exact identifier or by shared semantic concept."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:23
msgid "Building the chain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:25
msgid ""
"Drag a DMN card from the Available DMNs panel and drop it into the Chain "
"Composer. A placeholder zone appears as you drag; release to place the card. "
"Repeat for each subsequent DMN in the order you want them to execute."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:32
msgid "The validation panel below the composer updates after each drop:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:34
msgid ""
"**Green — DRD-compatible**: all variable connections are exact identifier "
"matches. The chain can be saved as a DRD for optimal performance."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:35
msgid ""
"**Amber — Sequential**: one or more connections rely on semantic concept "
"matching. The chain will execute as sequential API calls."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:36
msgid ""
"**Red — Invalid**: one or more required inputs have no match. Hover over the "
"red indicator to see which inputs are missing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:40
msgid "Providing inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:42
msgid ""
"The input form in the Configuration panel shows all variables the chain "
"needs from you — those that are not satisfied by the output of an earlier "
"DMN. Fill in each field with the appropriate value and type. Supported "
"types: `String`, `Integer`, `Double`, `Boolean`, `Date` (YYYY-MM-DD)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:44
msgid ""
"If a DMN has been published with example `schema:value` data in TriplyDB, "
"the input form pre-populates those values automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:48
msgid "Executing the chain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:50
msgid ""
"Click **Execute** when the chain is valid and inputs are filled. The "
"execution panel expands to show per-step progress. Each step shows which DMN "
"is executing, which inputs it received, and which outputs it produced. "
"Timing per step and total execution time appear on completion."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:52
msgid ""
"For sequential chains, output variables from each step are automatically "
"mapped to the input variables of the next step, including semantic variable "
"renaming where needed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:56
msgid "Reading results"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:58
msgid ""
"The final output panel shows the combined results from all steps. For DRD "
"chains, this is the output of the entry-point decision. For sequential "
"chains, it is the flattened output of the final DMN, together with "
"intermediate outputs from earlier steps."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:62
msgid "Removing a DMN from the chain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:64
msgid ""
"Click the trash icon on a DMN card in the Chain Composer to remove it. The "
"validation status updates immediately and the input form adjusts to reflect "
"the new chain."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:68
msgid "Reordering the chain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:70
msgid ""
"Drag cards within the Chain Composer to reorder them. The validation status "
"re-evaluates after the reorder."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:74
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\user-guide\\chain-building.md:74"
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:76
msgid ""
"[Saving & Executing DRDs]{1} — save a DRD-compatible chain as a reusable "
"template"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cchain-building.md:77
msgid ""
"[Semantic Analysis]{1} — understand why some chains require sequential "
"execution"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:1
msgid "Using the DMN Validator"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide explains how to validate DMN files before publishing them to "
"TriplyDB."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:7
msgid "Opening the validator"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:9
msgid ""
"Click the **shield icon** (🛡) in the left sidebar. The validator opens as a "
"full-panel view. Any files you have loaded remain in place when you switch "
"to other views and return."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:13
msgid "Loading files"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:15
msgid ""
"**Drag and drop** one or more `.dmn` or `.xml` files directly onto the drop "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:17
msgid ""
"**Browse** by clicking anywhere on the drop zone to open a file picker. The "
"picker accepts multiple file selection."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:19
msgid ""
"Files are read client-side — no content is sent to any server until you "
"click **Validate**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:21
msgid ""
"!!! note Only `.dmn` and `.xml` extensions are accepted. Other file types "
"are skipped with a brief warning toast."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:26
msgid "Running validation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:28
msgid ""
"**Single file.** Click the **Validate** button on an individual file card."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:30
msgid ""
"**All files at once.** Click **Validate all** in the header. This runs all "
"pending files concurrently — each card updates independently as results "
"arrive."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:32
msgid ""
"Validation calls `POST /v1/dmns/validate` on the shared backend. The file "
"content is sent as a JSON string. Results typically return within a few "
"hundred milliseconds."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:36
msgid "Reading the results"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:38
msgid "Summary badge"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:40
msgid "The top of each card shows either:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:42
msgid "🟢 **Valid** — no errors (warnings and info may still be present)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:43
msgid "🔴 **Invalid** — one or more errors detected"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:45
msgid ""
"Alongside the badge, count pills show the total number of errors (E), "
"warnings (W), and informational messages (I)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:47
msgid "Layer sections"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:49
msgid ""
"Below the summary, five collapsible layer rows show the per-layer status:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:51
msgid "A green ✓ and **OK** means the layer found no issues."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:52
msgid ""
"A coloured badge (e.g. **2W**, **1E**) means issues were found — click the "
"row to expand them."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:54
msgid "Issue rows"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:56
msgid "Each issue shows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:58
msgid "A severity icon (🔴 error / 🟡 warning / 🔵 info)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:59
msgid "A typed code (e.g. `INT-005`, `EXEC-001`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:60
msgid "A human-readable message"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:61
msgid ""
"Where applicable: an element reference (e.g. `<inputData "
"id=\"InputData_ingezetene_requirement\">`) and a line number"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:63
msgid ""
"Use the code to look up the detailed rationale in the [DMN Validation "
"Reference]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:67
msgid "Acting on results"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:69
msgid "Errors"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:71
msgid ""
"Errors must be resolved in your DMN authoring tool (Camunda Modeler, VS Code "
"DMN plugin, etc.) before the file is ready for deployment or publishing. "
"Common errors:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:73
msgid ""
"**BASE-PARSE** — the file is not valid XML. Open it in a text editor to "
"locate the syntax problem."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:74
msgid ""
"**BASE-NS** — the namespace does not match a known DMN version. Update the "
"`xmlns` attribute on `<definitions>`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:75
msgid ""
"**INT-005** — an `<inputData>` element exists but is not wired to any "
"decision. Either connect it or remove it in your modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:76
msgid ""
"**BIZ-008** — two rules in a `UNIQUE` or `ANY` table have identical input "
"entries. Operaton throws `DmnHitPolicyException` at runtime. Remove or "
"differentiate the duplicate rule."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:78
msgid "Warnings"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:80
msgid "Warnings are advisory. The most common ones for RONL publishing:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:82
msgid ""
"**BIZ-002 / BIZ-004** — `typeRef` is missing on an input expression or "
"output column. Add the FEEL type (e.g. `boolean`, `string`, `integer`) in "
"the modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:83
msgid ""
"**EXEC-001** — the CPRMV namespace is not declared. CPRMV attributes are "
"optional but recommended for RONL-compliant publishing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:84
msgid ""
"**BIZ-009** — a `UNIQUE` or `ANY` table contains a catch-all rule (all "
"inputs empty or `-`) alongside specific rules. Both the specific rule and "
"the catch-all fire for any matching input, violating the hit policy. Change "
"`hitPolicy` to `FIRST` and place the catch-all last."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:86
msgid "Informational messages"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:88
msgid ""
"Info messages flag quality improvements with no functional impact — for "
"example, missing `<textAnnotation>` content or absent CPRMV descriptive "
"attributes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:92
msgid "Removing files"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:94
msgid ""
"Click **×** on a file card to remove that file. Click **Clear all** in the "
"header to remove all files and reset the panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:98
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\user-guide\\dmn-validator.md:98"
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:100
msgid "Once all files are valid (or warnings have been reviewed and accepted):"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:102
msgid "Open the **CPSV Editor** and upload the DMN via the DMN tab."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:103
msgid "The editor will re-run validation inline — results should match."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdmn-validator.md:104
msgid "Deploy to Operaton and publish to TriplyDB."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\user-guide\\document-composer.md:1"
msgid "Document Composer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide walks through the complete workflow for creating a government "
"decision document (*beschikking*) template in the Document Composer, binding "
"it to process variables, and linking it to a BPMN process in the BPMN "
"Modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:7
msgid "Opening the Composer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:9
msgid ""
"Click **Document Composer** in the left sidebar (📄 icon). If no document "
"has been created yet, the canvas shows an empty state with a **Create New "
"Document** button. Click it, or use the **+** button in the left panel "
"header, to create your first document."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:13
msgid "Creating a document"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:15
msgid ""
"Click **+** in the document list header. A new document named `New document` "
"is created with all mandatory zones empty."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:16
msgid ""
"Double-click the document name to rename it (e.g. `Kapvergunning — "
"Beschikking`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:17
msgid ""
"The canvas opens automatically with the six mandatory zones visible. The "
"**Annex** zone is hidden by default."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:21
msgid "Adding blocks to zones"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:23
msgid ""
"The left panel has two tabs: **Documents** (the list) and **Content** (the "
"block library). Switch to **Content** to access the draggable block types."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:30
msgid ""
"Drag a **Rich text** block onto the **Body** zone. A TipTap editor appears "
"inline."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:31
msgid ""
"Type your decision text. Use the toolbar for bold, italic, headings, and "
"lists."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:32
msgid ""
"To reference a process variable, type `{{variableName}}` directly in the "
"text. The token is resolved at render time when MijnOmgeving fills in the "
"document."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:33
msgid ""
"Drag a **Variable** block onto the **Reference** zone for a standalone "
"display of a single variable (e.g. the file reference number)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:34
msgid ""
"Drag an **Image** block to add a TriplyDB-hosted asset such as a "
"municipality logo into the **Letterhead** zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:36
msgid "Reordering and moving blocks"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:38
msgid ""
"**Within a zone** — drag a block up or down to reorder it within the same "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:39
msgid ""
"**Between zones** — drag a block across zone boundaries to move it. The "
"target zone highlights when the block is over it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:40
msgid "**Delete a block** — click the trash icon on the block toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:44
msgid "Enabling the Annex zone"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:46
msgid ""
"At the bottom of the canvas, click **Add annex**. A seventh zone appears. "
"Remove it with **Remove annex**. Blocks in the annex are not lost when the "
"zone is toggled off and back on during the same session — but if you save "
"while the annex is off, its blocks are not persisted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:50
msgid "Binding variables"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:52
msgid ""
"Open the right panel by clicking the **Bindings** tab (visible when a "
"document is active)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:59
msgid ""
"Enter the **process key** in the field at the top (e.g. `AwbShellProcess`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:60
msgid ""
"Click **Discover Variables**. The panel queries the Operaton history API and "
"shows a chip for every variable found in completed process instances."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:61
msgid ""
"Click a chip to pre-fill the binding form. Adjust the **placeholder** field "
"if the token name in your text differs from the variable key."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:62
msgid ""
"Set **Source** to `process` for a live process variable, or `dmn_output` for "
"a DMN result variable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:63
msgid "Click **Add binding**. The binding appears in the list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdocument-composer.md:65
msgid ""
"You can also add bindings manually without using Discover Variables — fill "
"in the placeholder and variable key fields directly."
msgstr ""

